        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-num">01</div>
          <div>
            <div class="faq-q">I hold equity in 2 ASCs plus my surgical practice. How do they aggregate?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">Under <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-3.4-02/analyzing-returns-partnership-or-s-corporation" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Fannie Mae B3-3.4-02</a>, K-1 distributions from multiple entities aggregate as qualifying income when you hold sufficient ownership in each and each has 2-year 1120-S or 1065 history. We pull <a href="https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1120-s" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Form 1120-S</a> or 1065 per entity, all Schedule K-1s, your personal 1040, document ownership percentages, and qualify on the consolidated total.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-num">02</div>
          <div>
            <div class="faq-q">My call pay runs $185K annually. Will lenders count that?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">Yes, with documentation. Under <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-3.1-01/general-income-information" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Fannie Mae B3-3.1-01</a>, hospital call pay qualifies as variable W-2 income with 24-month average. We document the 24-month call coverage history through hospital pay stubs and the employment contract. Generalist lenders may treat call pay as "irregular" and exclude entirely; specialty lenders correctly apply 24-month variable income treatment.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-num">03</div>
          <div>
            <div class="faq-q">I&rsquo;m finishing fellowship and want to close before my August start date. Can I?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">Yes. Under Physician/Doctor Loan signed-contract qualifying, you can close on a home up to 60-90 days pre-start using the signed forward attending contract as income documentation. Particularly important for fellowship-finishing surgeons closing in July or August before September start dates. The signed contract documents future attending income before fellowship completion.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-num">04</div>
          <div>
            <div class="faq-q">My device consulting income with Stryker varies year-to-year. Does that hurt qualifying?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">Variable device consulting income smooths through the 24-month average requirement under <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-3.3-02/income-analysis-self-employed-borrowers" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Fannie Mae B3-3.3-02</a>. Significant year-over-year decline trend (greater than 25%) requires explanation but doesn&rsquo;t automatically disqualify. We document the consulting agreement structure with the device manufacturer and the multi-year pattern.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
