          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-num">08</div>
          <div>
            <div class="faq-q">I&rsquo;m buying into a surgical group as partner. How does that affect personal mortgage timing?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">The buy-in note becomes a personal DTI obligation when personally guaranteed. If the note is paid from partnership distributions, the monthly payment counts in DTI calculation. Sequencing matters: close personal mortgage either BEFORE the buy-in (qualifying on employed-period W-2) or AFTER 12-24 months of partner K-1 establishes the new income picture. For SBA-financed surgical group acquisitions, see our <a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/professional-services/business-acquirer/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">business acquirer mortgage guide</a>.</div>
          </div>
